                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0012/656</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-05">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>German Ambassador called in response to my suggestion that he exert his influence
                    in behalf of the negotiation of a treaty similar to those signed with the
                    twenty-seven other countries. Gave him copies of the British, French, Russian,
                    and Netherlands treaties. He expressed great interest in the subject and said he
                    would send them to Berlin and do what he could to induce his Government to join
                    in a similar treaty.</p>
            </div>
